 as parallel realities, laid bare by newly technologized “ears.” Deeply engaging, Interspecies Communication explores our attempts to cross the border between the human and non-human, to connect with non-humans in the depths of the oceans, the far reaches of the universe, or right under our own noses.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aExtraterrestrial beings. 0aHuman-animal communication. 0aHumanism. 0aMusicians, Black. 7aMUSIC / General.2bisacsh  aAfrofuturism, cosmic listening, Effective Altruism, interspecies communication, whale song.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079731240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226831350423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226831350/original  a978-3-11-079731-2  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles